"node":"text","body":"Fuel Tank - Installation"}],"target-id":"54043196914744459-2","target-base-id":"1386298507"}]}]}],"type":"dash"},{"node":"text","body":" "}],"metadata":{"ModelsTaxonomyLink":"DWB; DVB; DX4; DW4; DVY; DW; DVX; DV","MarketsTaxonomyLink":"All"},"type":"TextModule"},{"node":"textmodule","body":[{"node":"title","body":[{"node":"text","body":"Battery Installation DV; DVX; DW; DW4; DX4; DWB; DVB"}]},{"node":"text","body":"\r\n"},{"node":"ul","body":[{"node":"li","body":[{"node":"p","body":[{"node":"link","body":[{"node":"text","body":"Battery - Installation"}],"target-id":"261208779251128203-2","target-base-id":"863639435"}]}]}],"type":"dash"},{"node":"text","body":" "}],"metadata":{"ModelsTaxonomyLink":"DVB; DWB; DX4; DW4; DW; DVX; DV","MarketsTaxonomyLink":"All"},"type":"TextModule"},{"node":"textmodule","body":[{"node":"title","body":[{"node":"text","body":"Sidestand (Unordered list)"}]},{"node":"text","body":"\r\n"},{"node":"ul","body":[{"node":"li","body":[{"node":"p","body":[{"node":"text","body":"Lower the motorcycle to the ground and park it on the side stand."}]}]}],"type":"dash"},{"node":"text","body":"\r\n"}],"metadata":{"MarketsTaxonomyLink":"All"},"type":"TextModule"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"}],"ancestors":["1342357259"],"parent":"1342357259","lastUpdate":"2023-03-03T09:38:38.000Z","metadata":{"markets":["All"],"_id":"66695efb644bf0afb184b7fb"},"search":["Engine - Installation","Make sure the motorcycle is stabilised and adequately supported.","A correctly supported motorcycle will help prevent it from falling.","An unstable motorcycle may fall, causing injury to the operator or damage to the motorcycle.","Ensure the alternator harness, ignition switch cable and air temperature sensor cable are routed as noted during removal. ","Locate the engine to the frame aligning the engine mounting points with the corresponding positions on the frame.","Attach the brake lines to the brake line tidy.","Brake line from ABS modulator to front master cylinder. ","Brake line from ABS modulator to front brake caliper","Brake line tidy","Install and tighten the engine mounting bolts in the following 3 stages.","Stage 1","Insert the cylinder head left hand front mounting bolt with washer between the bolt and the frame.","Insert the cylinder head right hand front mounting bolt fit a new lock nut but not fully tighten at this stage.","Install the lower rear crankcase mounting bolt from the right hand side of the motorcycle, with the spacer between the frame and the crankcase on the right hand side, and the spacer between the frame adjuster and the engine on the left hand side.","Insert the crankcase rear upper mounting bolt from the right hand side. Do not fit the washer and new lock nut at this stage.","Stage 2","Partially withdraw the crankcase rear lower mounting bolt and tighten the frame adjuster to ","5 Nm"," using ","T3880377 - Engine Mounting Adjuster",". Refit the bolt and washer.","Partially withdraw the crankcase rear upper mounting bolt and tighten the frame adjuster to ","5 Nm"," using ","T3880377 - Engine Mounting Adjuster",". Refit the bolt and washer.","Counter hold the cylinder head front right hand cylinder head mounting nut and tighten the bolt to ","24 Nm",".","Withdraw the cylinder head left hand mounting bolt and tighten the frame adjuster to ","5 Nm"," using ","T3880377 - Engine Mounting Adjuster",".","Fit the washer and a new lock nut to the crankcase lower rear mounting bolt. Counter hold the bolt and tighten the nut to ","80 Nm",".","Fit the washer and a new lock nut to the crankcase upper rear mounting bolt. Counter hold the bolt and tighten the nut to ","80 Nm",".","Fit a new lock nut to the cylinder head front right hand mounting bolt. Counter hold the nut and tighten the bolt to ","105 Nm",".","Fit the washer and a new lock nut to the cylinder head front left hand mounting bolt. Counter hold the nut and tighten the bolt to ","105 Nm",".","Swinging arm adjuster","Upper rear crankcase adjuster","Cylinder head frame adjuster","Lower rear crankcase adjuster","Stage 3","While supporting the swinging arm, remove the swinging arm spindle and partially insert it from the right hand side. Tighten the frame adjuster to ","6 Nm",".","While supporting the swinging arm, remove the swinging arm spindle and fully insert it with the washer from the left hand side.","Fit the washer and a new lock nut to the swinging arm spindle. Counter hold the spindle and tighten the nut to ","110 Nm","Install the swinging arm spindle finishers as noted for removal and tighten the fixing to ","1 Nm",".","Route the starter motor cable, crankshaft position sensor and gear position sensor cables behind the harness guide as noted during removal. Tighten the upper harness guide fixing to ","4 Nm",".","Connect the electrical connectors as follows:","Gear position sensor,","Crankshaft position sensor,","Oil pressure switch.","Refit the starter solenoid bracket to the crankcase bracket with two fixings and tighten to ","5 Nm",".","Gear position sensor connector","Crankshaft position sensor connector","Starter motor cable","Starter motor solenoid","Starter solenoid bracket","Crankcase bracket","Refit the starter motor cable to the solenoid, tighten the fixing to ","5 Nm",".","Secure the harness guide to the crankcase and tighten the fixing to ","4 Nm",".","Fixing","Harness guide","Refit the packaging cover and secure with three fixings. Tighten the upper two fixings to ","6 Nm"," and the lower fixing to ","3 Nm",".","Packaging cover","Fixings","Lower fixing","Secure the intake shield to the packaging cover and tighten the fixing to ","6 Nm",".","Intake shield fixing","Intake shield","Packaging cover","Refit the drive chain to the front sprocket and adjust (see ","Final Drive Chain Adjustment",").","Fit the coolant expansion tank mounting and tighten its fixings to ","4 Nm",".","Rear brake fluid reservoir lock nut","Fixings","Alternator harness","Attach the rear brake fluid reservoir to the mounting plate and tighten the new lock nut to ","3 Nm",".","Rear brake fluid reservoir","Lock nut","Refit the coolant expansion tank to its mountings and tighten the new lock nuts to ","3 Nm",".","Lock nuts","Coolant expansion tank","Fit the sprocket cover and evenly and progressively tighten the fixings to ","9 Nm",".","Refit and adjust the clutch cable (see ","Clutch Cable - Installation",").","Connect the following electrical connectors:","Coolant temperature sensor;","Fuel injectors;","Spark plug leads.","Refit the radiator (see ","Radiator - Installation",").","Refit the throttle body (see ","Throttle Body - Installation",").","Refill the engine with oil (see ","Engine Oil and Filter Renew",").","Refill the engine with coolant (see ","Coolant Replacement - Filling",").","Refit the exhaust system (see ","Exhaust Header Pipes - Installation"," and ","Exhaust Silencer - Installation",").","Refit the left and right hand frame cradles (see ","Cradle Assemblies - Installation",").","Refit the alternator regulator/rectifier (see ","Alternator Regulator/Rectifier - Installation",").","Airbox - Installation","Side Panels","Fuel Tank - Installation","Battery - Installation","Lower the motorcycle to the ground and park it on the side stand."],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType08","createdAt":"2024-06-12T08:40:27.269Z","updatedAt":"2024-06-12T08:40:27.269Z","__v":0}